overview: The user wanted to elevate the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, moving beyond a generic look to a more professional and
  calming aesthetic. The assistant began by thoroughly reviewing the existing
  design, identifying issues with the color palette, layout, and component
  styling. A new sleep-themed color palette was introduced, and key UI
  components like the progress bar, checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were
  redesigned for a more polished feel. The main questionnaire form and intro
  section were enhanced with subtle decorative elements and improved visual
  hierarchy. Crucially, the new styling was consistently applied across all
  questionnaire sections and the final report, transforming the app's overall
  aesthetic to be more inviting and appropriate for a sleep health application.
  The changes were verified through code review and browser inspection.
